# HyperZ Framework — Cursor AI Rules
# This file is automatically read by Cursor AI when working in this project.

# Project: Laravel-inspired Express.js + TypeScript API framework
# Runtime: Node.js ≥ 20, TypeScript strict mode, ES Modules
# Entry: server.ts → app.ts → service provider boot lifecycle

# CODING RULES:
# 1. Use TypeScript strict mode — avoid `any` types
# 2. Use `.js` extensions in ALL import paths (ESM output)
# 3. Use `type` keyword for type-only imports
# 4. Application code goes in app/ — never edit src/ (framework core)
# 5. Use the CLI (`npx hyperz make:<type> <Name>`) to scaffold files
# 6. Route files in app/routes/ are auto-loaded — no manual registration
# 7. Read env vars via env('KEY', 'default') helper, not process.env
# 8. Bind controller methods in routes: controller.method.bind(controller)

# NAMING CONVENTIONS:
# Controllers: PascalCase + Controller suffix (ProductController)
# Models: PascalCase singular (Product)
# Migrations: snake_case timestamped (20260101_create_products_table.ts)
# Seeders: PascalCase + Seeder suffix (ProductSeeder)
# Jobs: PascalCase (SendWelcomeEmail)
# Route files: lowercase (api.ts)

# FRAMEWORK PATTERNS:
# Controllers extend Controller from src/http/Controller.js
# Models extend Model from src/database/Model.js
# Jobs extend BaseJob from src/queue/QueueManager.js
# Use HyperZRouter from src/http/Router.js for routing
# Use validate() from src/validation/Validator.js with Zod schemas
# Use router.resource('/path', controller) for CRUD routes

# RESPONSE HELPERS (in controllers):
# this.success(res, data, message) → 200
# this.created(res, data, message) → 201
# this.error(res, message, status) → error
# this.noContent(res) → 204
# this.paginate(res, data, total, page, perPage)

# DEV SERVER:
